Title: Why Your Lambda Functions Need a Structural Makeover
Description:
Hi, I'm James Eastham, In this video, I'll share how to structure your Lambda functions for modularity and longevity using Ports and Adapters architecture. 

Avoid the pitfalls of monolithic code by separating business logic from infrastructure concerns.

Learn why a clean separation of concerns is vital for maintainable and adaptable code, regardless of whether you're using .NET, Node.js, Python, or Rust. By the end, you'll understand how to make your code more testable, scalable, and adaptable to changes in deployment environments.

Title: My tips on giving technical talks
Description: I've been giving talks at meetups and conferences for a few years now. I started off after the encouragement of my friends giving their own talk and looking so cool doing it! It's taken a while but I think I'm at a stage now where I'm not only good at it (at least I hope so üòÖ) but I feel confident and comfortable while doing it. I want everyone to have that same confidence and I want to hear ALL OF YOU giving talks too! You have stories to tell, lessons to share and experience to pass on. So here is my learnings on how I approach giving a talk in front of a crowd of techies, mainly focussed on technical talks but most of this should apply to most public speaking.
